itools 0.62.5 (2010/1X/XX)
==========================

itools is a Python library, it groups a number of packages into a single
meta-package for easier development and deployment:

  itools.abnf             itools.i18n             itools.rss
  itools.core             itools.ical             itools.srx
  itools.csv              itools.log              itools.stl
  itools.database         itools.loop             itools.tmx
  itools.datatypes        itools.odf              itools.uri
  itools.fs               itools.office           itools.web
  itools.gettext          itools.pdf              itools.workflow
  itools.git              itools.pkg              itools.xliff
  itools.handlers         itools.python           itools.xml
  itools.html             itools.relaxng          itools.xmlfile
  itools.http             itools.rest

The documentation, written using Sphinx [1], is now included in the
itools source, within the 'docs/' folder (previously it was in a
separate package). The URL has also changed, now it is:

  http://www.hforge.org/itools/docs

The ipkg-docs.py script has been added, it is used to compile the
documentation.

There have been many small enhancements and bug fixes, including:

  #886 (i18n)     Fix select_language in some corner cases
 #1032 (gettext)  Support for HTML in <MSG> objects
 #1044 (web)      Refactor authentication code
 #1051 (odf)      Support ODF 1.2
 #1058 (handlers) Now 'checkid' supports Turkish characters

[1] http://sphinx.pocoo.org/


